    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-09-11T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-09-11T15:00:00-05:00" n="411"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.48B/51: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Woods</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-09-11T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 11, 1923—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>150. Your September 6, received September 10, regarding delivery of relief
                    supplies to Japanese authorities.</p>
                <p>The Department and the Red-Cross share your views as expressed in the above
                    telegram and feel that all relief supplies should be delivered to the Japanese
                    authorities. Department is transmitting to you today a telegram from the
                        Red-Cross<note n="26" xml:id="d411fn26">Not printed.</note> stating
                    specifically its desires in the matter of administering relief measures.</p>
                <p>You will disregard the Department’s 142, September 8, 11-a.m.<note n="26"
                        xml:id="d411fn27">Not printed.</note> and be guided by the Red-Cross’
                    telegram which is being transmitted to you today by the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
